## \file gnetlist2.in
## Wrapper script for invoking the gEDA netlister.
#
# As opposed to the <tt>gnetlist</tt> command, <tt>xorn netlist</tt>
# doesn't read the old-style Guile configuration files \c gafrc and \c
# gnetlistrc and doesn't support the Guile-specific command line
# options \c -l, \c -m, and \c -c.  This wrapper script runs the
# configuration files, detects the Guile-specific command line options
# and translates them into a <tt>xorn netlist</tt> invocation and can
# be used as a drop-in replacement for <tt>gnetlist</tt> in most
# situations.
#
# It does *not* read the new-style configuration file \c geda.conf,
# and it does *not* support Guile functions as a symbol library.

